.TH d2b-launch 1 1970-01-01 "d2b 0.0.0-bootstrap" "d2b CLI"
.SH NAME
d2b-launch \- launch a trusted configured workload item
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBd2b launch\fR <\fITARGET\fR> [\fB--item\fR <\fIID\fR>] [\fB--json\fR|\fB--human\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Resolves argv-free launcher metadata through d2bd, then dispatches the selected
private configured item through its provider. No command, uid, environment,
working directory, path, process id, or unit name is accepted from the caller.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--item\fR <\fIID\fR>
Select a configured item. Without this option, the declared default or sole item
is selected; multiple items without a default are rejected.
.TP
\fB--json\fR
Emit the typed launch result as JSON.
.TP
\fB--human\fR
Force human-readable output.
